com.link_intersystems.lang.reflect.criteria

Class MemberCriteria<T extends Member>

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.link_intersystems.lang.reflect.criteria.ElementCriteria<T>
      • com.link_intersystems.lang.reflect.criteria.MemberCriteria<T>
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Cloneable

    public class MemberCriteria<T extends Member>
extends ElementCriteria<T>
    Iterate over Members or AnnotatedElements that match the criteria specified by a MemberCriteria.

    Examples

    Iterate over all public abstract methods, in method names order, whose name's match the pattern "add.*" starting at class ArrayList.

     MemberCriteria memberCriteria = new MemberCriteria();
 memberCriteria.withAccess(AccessType.PUBLIC);
 memberCriteria.withModifiers(Modifier.ABSTRACT);
 memberCriteria.membersOfType(Method.class);
 memberCriteria.setMemberIterateOrder(MemberNameComparator.INSTANCE);
 memberCriteria.named(Pattern.compile("add.*"));

 ClassCriteria classCriteria = new ClassCriteria();
 Iterable<Class<?>> classIterable = classCriteria.getIterable(ArrayList.class);
 Iterable<Member> memberIterable = memberCriteria.getIterable(classIterable);

 Iterator<Member> criteriaIterator = memberIterable.iterator();

    Get the first public method that has the same signature as List.subList(int, int) starting at ArrayList traversing only the class hierarchy (omit interfaces).

     MemberCriteria memberCriteria = new MemberCriteria();
 memberCriteria.setResult(Selection.FIRST);
 memberCriteria.membersOfType(Method.class);

 Method method = List.class.getDeclaredMethod("subList", int.class, int.class);

 memberCriteria.add(new SignaturePredicate(method));

 ClassCriteria classCriteria = new ClassCriteria();
 classCriteria.setTraverseOrder(TraverseOrder.SUPERCLASSES_ONLY);
 Iterable<Class<?>> classIterable = classCriteria.getIterable(ArrayList.class);
 Iterable<Member> memberIterable = memberCriteria.getIterable(classIterable);

 Iterator<Member> criteriaIterator = memberIterable.iterator();
 Member member = criteriaIterator.next();
 Method firstMatch = (Method) member;
 Method declaredMethod = AbstractList.class.getDeclaredMethod("subList", int.class, int.class);
 assertEquals(declaredMethod, firstMatch);
 assertFalse(criteriaIterator.hasNext());

      • setMemberIterateOrder

        public void setMemberIterateOrder(Comparator<Member> iterateOrderComparator)
        Set the order in which Member are iterated. The order is defined by the Comparator. The Member order is determined per declaring class. Therefore the member iterate order only determines how Members of the same declaring class are iterated. So it does NOT affect the order of Members of different classes (global order).
        Parameters:
        iterateOrderComparator - the member comparator that orders the members.
        Since:
        1.0.0;

      • add

        public void add(Predicate<T> predicate)
        Use the defined predicate as a filter when searching for elements. Multiple calls to this method will combine the predicates with a logical 'and' operator. The type of objects that the Predicate must be able to handle is defined by subclasses.

        The Predicate must handle Method objects in it's Predicate.test(Object) method.

        Overrides:
        add in class ElementCriteria<T extends Member>
        Parameters:
        predicate - the predicate to use when filtering elements.
        Since:
        1.0.0;

      • getAnnotatedElementIterable

        public Iterable<? extends AnnotatedElement> getAnnotatedElementIterable(Iterable<Class<?>> classIterable,
                                                                        MemberCriteria.IterateStrategy iterateStrategy)
        Parameters:
        classIterable - the class Iterable that defines the classes that are iterated to look for members that match this MemberCriteria.
        iterateStrategy - the order in which the AnnotatedElement types selected by this MemberCriteria are iterated through. In contrast to the getIterable(Iterable) method the MemberCriteria.IterateStrategy allows you to iterate also through elements that the selected Members are declared on.
        Returns:
        an Iterable that creates Iterators that iterate through AnnotatedElements as defined by this MemberCriteria using the given iterate strategy.
        Since:
        1.0.0;
